  <front>
   <head>Democritus and Heraclitus.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="sestet">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">, dear Droll, revisit Earth,</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">And with our Follies glut Thy heighten'd Mirth:</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Sad , serious Wretch, return,</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">In louder Grief our greater Crimes to mourn.</l>
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Between You both I unconcern'd stand by:</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Hurt, can I laugh? and Honest, need I cry?</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
